main event: Observers saw a star-like, red and white object in the sky near Duluth on January 3, 1966.
interesting points: The object was first sighted at 270-280 degrees, 45 degrees above the horizon and faded out at 265 degrees, 30 degrees above the horizon., The sighting lasted for approximately 3 seconds., The Quadrantid meteor shower reached its peak activity on the same date., The observation was made by military personnel., The conclusion drawn was that the sighting was attributed to a meteor.
